cs.WEB, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SD, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on improving Web performance by identifying and eliding superfluous JavaScript code. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.WEB, which deals with topics related to the World Wide Web. The paper also involves designing a systematic approach for website developers, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper involves measuring and analyzing data, which could fall under the categories of software development (cs.SD) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
